<br>
The truth, I think, is that PoP zones generally have a lack of loot compared to pre-PoP zones.  I mean, most yard trash in the tier 1 planes drop worthless items that are many times worth less than the cash loots that they drop.  Compare this to CT, Chardok, Sebilis, Velketors, or even Maiden's Eye.  The above mentioned zones have excellent upgrades available to players who might never raid, as long as they have a group willing to go deep and do some named mobs.  This isn't true in much of PoP - you have your &quot;semi-boss&quot; mobs that spawn every 3 hours or so that drop passeable loot and you have your boss mobs that drop decent loot.  Other than that, most other loot in the planes leaves something to be desired (look at the decayed bone idol or the twink gear that drops off of factory mobs that require you to kill a PoI dragon to &quot;legitimately&quot; enter), especially considering their difficulty versus something like chardok or sebilis.<br>
<br>
This raises several problems, one of which is melees wanting to roll on caster parchments, because other than caster parchments your average pick-up group probably won't find anything else worthwhile.  Put a couple of Heirophant cloaks/FT3 boots/Tranquil staves/etc. on the tougher mobs and this problem is solved.  Melees will be happy to camp spots that isn't the &quot;best exp&quot; (as melees do now), and casters will find that they are once again entitled to parchments.  It's really not that hard of a thing for VI to implement, but they didn't.  /shrug<br>
<br>
Another problem is the loot dynamics in general.  It seems to me that VI underestimates the difficulty of some of their PoP mobs/rings while overestimating the difficulty of some of their Luclin/Velious uber mobs.  They put one of the best crowns in the game on King Tormax, but Tormax is a pushover compared to POP ubers.  This isn't limited to PoP, of course.  Take a look at the CT ring, for instance, or the fix-maybe-in-next-two-years Acrylia rings...<br>
<br>
Generally, I'd like to see an overhaul and reevaluation of risk vs. reward of most PoP zones, from the smallest yard trash up to the most uber of uber mobs.  Oh and, please, put something other than Focus IV effects on caster loots...  It's getting as redundant as FT was for Luclin.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
